creator: PIXEL MILLER
descriptionHtml:
Elementium Periodic Table app is the perfect tool for anyone interested in chemistry, science, and the elements. With a user-friendly interface, the app provides a wealth of information about each element, including its properties, history, and uses.

One of the most exciting features of Elementium is the 3D model of each element. With just a few taps, users can explore the structure of every atom, seeing the arrangement of electrons, protons, and neutrons in a realistic, interactive way. This feature brings the elements to life, making it easier to understand their behavior and properties.

This Periodic Table also offers 3D visualizations of orbitals, which provide a deeper understanding of how electrons move around the nucleus of an atom. By seeing these patterns in a 3D environment, users can gain a more intuitive understanding of how electrons occupy different energy levels, and how these levels determine the chemical properties of an element.

Another powerful tool in Elementium is the emission spectrum feature. This allows users to see the unique set of colors emitted by an element when it is excited, such as when it is heated or placed in an electric field. By analyzing these colors, scientists can identify unknown elements, and gain insights into the behavior of different substances.

The app also offers a wealth of information on each element, including its atomic weight, melting and boiling points, and other key data. Users can search for specific elements, or browse by category, such as metals, nonmetals, or noble gases. Each element has its own page, with detailed information on its discovery, history, and uses in industry and everyday life.


Whether you're a student, a teacher, or simply curious about the natural world, Elementium Periodic Table app is the perfect tool for exploring the elements and the science behind them. With its 3D models, visualizations, and wealth of information, it provides a unique and engaging way to learn about the building blocks of the universe.
